        "title": "feat(search): add turbovec vector backend",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds a configurable semantic vector backend for gitcrawl.\n\n- adds `vector_backend = \"exact\"` with `GITCRAWL_VECTOR_BACKEND` override\n- routes backend selection through semantic search, `neighbors`, and TUI neighbor loading\n- documents optional `turbovec` usage and its dimensions-divisible-by-8 contract\n- updates gitcrawl to released `github.com/openclaw/crawlkit v0.12.0`\n- keeps large or unsupported TurboVec searches correct by falling back to exact search instead of failing\n\n## Verification\n\n- `go test ./internal/vector`\n- `go test ./internal/cli -run 'TestTUILoadNeighbors|TestTUILoadNeighborsUsesConfiguredBackend|TestTUIUpdateCoversMainKeysAfterMenuBoundary' -count=1`\n- `GOWORK=off go test -count=1 ./...`\n- `GOWORK=off go test -race ./...`\n- `GOWORK=off go build ./cmd/gitcrawl`\n- `GOWORK=off go vet ./...`\n- `autoreview --mode local`\n- `autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main`\n- temp-home binary smokes using a built binary:\n  - `gitcrawl --help`\n  - `gitcrawl --version`\n  - `gitcrawl metadata --json`\n  - `gitcrawl status --json`\n  - `gitcrawl tui --json`\n",
